'''Bunsen''' may refer to: * [[Christian Charles Josias Bunsen]] (1791–1860), Prussian diplomat and scholar * [[Frances Bunsen]] (1791–1876), or Baroness Bunsen, Welsh painter and author, wife of Christian Charles Josias Bunsen * [[Robert Bunsen]] (1811–1899), German chemist, after whom is named: ** [[Bunsen burner]] ** [[Bunsen cell]] ** [[Bunsen (crater)|Bunsen crater]] on the moon ** [[10361 Bunsen]], an asteroid ** [[Bunsen Reaction]] ** The [[Bunsen–Kirchhoff Award]], a German award for spectroscopy * Sir [[Maurice de Bunsen]] (1852–1932), British diplomat * [[Dr. Bunsen Honeydew]], fictional character from the Muppet Show
